In[6]:
num_cols = df.select_dtypes(include=np.number).columns
cat_cols = df.select_dtypes(include="object").columns

df[num_cols] = df[num_cols].fillna(df[num_cols].median())
df[cat_cols] = df[cat_cols].fillna(df[cat_cols].mode().iloc[0])

5. Feature Engineering

In[7]:
df["Engagement_Intensity"] = df["watch_hours"] / (df["last_login_days"] + 1)
df["Support_Ratio"] = df["number_of_profiles"] / (df["last_login_days"] + 1)

11. Encoding and Scaling

In[13]:
df_encoded = pd.get_dummies(df, drop_first=True)

# Use the correct target column name
X = df_encoded.drop("churned", axis=1)
y = df_encoded["churned"]

scaler = StandardScaler()
X_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X)

12. Train-Test Split and SMOTE

In[14]:
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(
    X_scaled, y, test_size=0.3, random_state=42, stratify=y
)

smote = SMOTE(random_state=42)
X_train_sm, y_train_sm = smote.fit_resample(X_train, y_train)

13. Model Training and Evaluation

In[15]:
models = {
    "Logistic Regression": LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000),
    "Decision Tree": DecisionTreeClassifier(),
    "Random Forest": RandomForestClassifier(),
    "Gradient Boosting": GradientBoostingClassifier(),
    "SVM": SVC(probability=True)
}

results = []

for name, model in models.items():
    model.fit(X_train_sm, y_train_sm)
    y_pred = model.predict(X_test)
    y_prob = model.predict_proba(X_test)[:,1]
    
    results.append([
        name,
        accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred),
        precision_score(y_test, y_pred),
        recall_score(y_test, y_pred),
        f1_score(y_test, y_pred),
        roc_auc_score(y_test, y_prob)
    ])
In[16]:
results_df = pd.DataFrame(
    results,
    columns=["Model", "Accuracy", "Precision", "Recall", "F1", "ROC_AUC"]
)
